translated: Falk, Gunnar Fredrik, high school teacher, Skövde, b. May 30, 1885 in Transtrand, Kopparb. 1st district, son of vicar J.P. Falk and Ida Björlin. Married in 1936 to Maj Sjöberg. Children: Kerstin b. 1940, Gudrun b. 1943, Brita b. 1944. Graduated from Falun Teacher's College in 1906, bachelor's degree from Uppsala University in 1912, master's degree in 1918, probationary year at Norra Real in Stockholm in 1919. Temporary teacher in Eksjö from 1912-1913, at Gothenburg West High School from 1913-1914, permanent teacher there from 1915-1916, temporary subject teacher in Hässleholm in 1914, temporary teacher in Karlskrona from 1916-1917, at Östra Real in Stockholm in 1917, temporary subject teacher in Ludvika in 1918, temporary teacher in Oskarshamn from 1919-1920. Permanent teacher at Katarina High School in Stockholm from 1920-1932, teacher of German, history, social science, and geography at Skövde high school since 1932. Group leader for school youth alpine tours, among others from 1932-1934, Swedish-German school youth exchange in the summers of 1931-1932 and 1937, chief of Skövde Scout Corps from 1933-1941, deputy chairman of the Skidfrämj. in Skövde. Traveled to Germany in 1922, 1923, 1929, 1931, 1932, and 1937, and to Nordkap in 1933. Member of the Swedish Scout Association, Skidfrämjande SM, and Dipli.
